    "(3) Our findings reveal that NLI models pre-trained for numerical understanding outperform generic models in factchecking numerical claims by up to 11.78%.",
    "We also show that smaller models fine-tuned on numerical claims outperform larger models like GPT-3.5-Turbo under zero-shot and few-shot scenarios.",
    "(4) We also assess the quality of questions decomposed by ClaimDecomp and ProgramFC for numerical claims, using both automated metrics and manual evaluation.",
    "We make our dataset and code available here https://github.com/ factiverse/QuanTemp.",
    "The process of automated fact-checking is typically structured as a pipeline encompassing three key stages: claim detection, evidence retrieval, and verdict prediction, the latter often involving stance detection or natural language inference (NLI) tasks [8,15,56]."
